main event: On June 7, 1960, several witnesses reported observing unidentified flying objects in Champaign, Illinois.
interesting points: The objects were described as having a round shape and emitted a brilliant white light., The objects were observed to maneuver in unusual patterns and moved at extreme speeds., One observer, a retired military pilot, noted that the objects were larger than stars but smaller than small planes., The sightings lasted anywhere from 1 to 30 minutes, with no sound associated., Analyzed film suggested the object was likely a meteor due to its high velocity and brightness.
witness description: various observers including military personnel and civilians
